{"ts": "2026-06-08T04:11:49.573089+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: b7f48297d45c03a601414545c00525212f3a6fe8)", "id": "lc_c056973f-1a3c-4d18-b2bb-bb9ac66e926e"}, {"type": "text", "text": "name: Deploy to ECR\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [ master ]\n\njobs:\n  build:\n    name: Build Image\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n\n\n    steps:\n      - name: Check out code\n        uses: actions/checkout@v2\n\n      - name: Configure AWS credentials\n        uses: aws-actions/configure-aws-credentials@v1\n        with:\n          aws-access-key-id: ${{ secrets.AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID }}\n          aws-secret-access-key: ${{ secrets.AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY }}\n          aws-region: ${{ secrets.AWS_REGION }}\n\n      - name: Login to Amazon ECR\n        id: login-ecr\n        uses: aws-actions/amazon-ecr-login@v1\n\n      - name: Build, tag, and push image to Amazon ECR\n        env:\n          ECR_REGISTRY: ${{ steps.login-ecr.outputs.registry }}\n          ECR_REPOSITORY: lantron-ecr-b5b2b12\n          IMAGE_TAG: react-admin\n        run: |\n          docker build -t $ECR_REGISTRY/$ECR_REPOSITORY:$IMAGE_TAG .\n          docker push $ECR_REGISTRY/$ECR_REPOSITORY:$IMAGE_TAG", "id": "lc_93d30140-5c3c-45b8-a2c3-6f1f1c6ce8c6"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "ce753797-57b7-41de-8ac5-04e8ca58ab7e", "tool_call_id": "call_00_2fxf1mNTlHNh2ghsbIMh4974", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T04:12:13.001623+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on the repository contents, here is a comprehensive summary of how to run, build, and preview this React admin application.\n\n---\n\n## Project Overview\n\n- **Stack:** Vite + React 18 + TypeScript + Material UI (MUI)\n- **Package manager:** Yarn (lock file present)\n- **Environment configs:** Stored in `envs/` directory, loaded based on `NODE_ENV`\n\n---\n\n## 1. Setup / Initialization\n\n```bash\n# Install dependencies\nyarn install\n\n# (Optional) Copy the local env file to the project root\ncp envs/.env.local .env\n```\n\nAlternatively, the repo includes a **Taskfile** (`Taskfile.yaml`). The `task init` command automates setup:\n```bash\ntask init\n```\nThis installs global npm tools (`commitizen`, `standard-version`, etc.), copies `envs/.env.local` → `.env`, and runs `yarn install`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Running Locally (Development)\n\n```bash\nyarn dev\n```\n- Sets `NODE_ENV=local` via `cross-env`\n- Vite loads environment variables from `.env` (or falls back to `envs/.env.local`)\n- Dev server runs with HMR over WebSocket, **CORS enabled**\n- Default port: **10086** (configurable via `VITE_PORT` in `.env` / `.env.local`)\n- Host: `local.lantron.ltd` (as per `.env.local`)\n\n```bash\n# Staging dev server (if needed)\nyarn dev:stg\n```\n- Sets `NODE_ENV=stg`, loads `envs/.env.stg`\n\n---\n\n## 3. Building for Different Environments\n\n| Command          | Mode / Env       | Env File Loaded      | Purpose                |\n|------------------|------------------|----------------------|------------------------|\n| `yarn build`     | `--mode prod`    | `envs/.env.prod`     | Default production     |\n| `yarn build:stg` | `--mode test`    | `envs/.env.stg`      | Staging environment    |\n| `yarn build:prod`| `--mode production` | `envs/.env.prod`  | Explicit production    |\n\nAll builds output to the **`dist/`** directory (configured via `VITE_OUTPUT_DIR`).\n\nKey environment variables per environment:\n\n| Variable            | Local                     | Staging                    | Production              |\n|---------------------|---------------------------|----------------------------|-------------------------|\n| `NODE_ENV`          | `local`                   | `stg`                      | `prod`                  |\n| `VITE_BUILD_ENV`    | `development`             | `production`               | `production`            |\n| `VITE_HOST`         | `local.lantron.ltd`       | `stg.lantron.ltd`          | `lantron.ltd`           |\n| `VITE_PORT`         | `10086`                   | `10086`                    | _(empty)_               |\n| `VITE_BASE_URL`     | `./`                      | `./`                       | `./`                    |\n| `VITE_APP_BASE_API` | `https://mock.local...`   | `https://mock.stg...`      | `https://mock.lantron.ltd` |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Previewing the Built App\n\n```bash\nyarn serve\n```\n- Runs `vite preview --host` to serve the `dist/` directory locally\n- Useful for verifying a production build before deployment\n\n---\n\n## 5. Docker Build & Deployment\n\nA multi-stage **Dockerfile** is provided:\n\n```bash\ndocker build -t vite-react-ts-admin .\ndocker run -p 80:80 vite-react-ts-admin\n```\n\n- **Stage 1:** Node LTS Alpine — installs dependencies, runs `yarn build`\n- **Stage 2:** Nginx Alpine — copies `dist/` to `/usr/share/nginx/html`, uses custom `nginx.conf` (SPA-friendly with `try_files` fallback to `index.html`)\n- Exposes port **80**\n\n### CI/CD: Amazon ECR\n- GitHub Actions workflow (`.github/workflows/push-image.yml`) triggers on push to `master`\n- Builds the Docker image, tags it, and pushes to **Amazon ECR** (registry: `lantron-ecr-b5b2b12`, image tag: `react-admin`)\n\n---\n\n## 6. Netlify Deployment\n\nThe `netlify.toml` configures SPA redirects:\n```toml\n[[redirects]]\n  from = \"/*\"\n  to = \"/\"\n  status = 200\n```\nDeploy by connecting the repo to Netlify — it auto-detects the build command (`yarn build`) and publish directory (`dist`).\n\n---\n\n## 7. GitHub Pages Deployment\n\n```bash\nyarn deploy\n```\nUses `gh-pages` to publish the `dist/` folder to the repository's GitHub Pages branch (configured homepage: `https://reactZone.github.io/vite-react-ts-admin`).\n\n---\n\n## Quick Reference Cheat Sheet\n\n| Task                         | Command              |\n|------------------------------|----------------------|\n| Install dependencies         | `yarn install`       |\n| Start dev server (local)     | `yarn dev`           |\n| Start dev server (staging)   | `yarn dev:stg`       |\n| Build (production)           | `yarn build`         |\n| Build (staging)              | `yarn build:stg`     |\n| Build (explicit production)  | `yarn build:prod`    |\n| Preview built app            | `yarn serve`         |\n| Lint                         | `yarn lint`          |\n| Auto-fix lint issues         | `yarn fix`           |\n| Deploy to GitHub Pages       | `yarn deploy`        |\n| Docker build & run           | `docker build -t app . && docker run -p 80:80 app` |", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1699, "prompt_tokens": 8691, "total_tokens": 10390, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 388, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 8320}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 8320, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 371}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-pro", "system_fingerprint": "fp_9954b31ca7_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "c587e00f-0ac6-48e5-b04a-6834a11d8ac6", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea56d-fdc6-77b1-a12a-b0f3989bb709-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8691, "output_tokens": 1699, "total_tokens"